    <h1><b>Chandigarh</b></h1>
    <hr />
    <p>
   The magnificent city of Chandigarh has a fabulous history as a city was the vision of our first Prime Minister, Pandit Jawaharlal Nehru. The grand city was designed by popular French architect Le Corbusier. The city reflects the modern architecture of 20th century.
   <br />
   The name of city is adopted from the temple called "Chandi Mandir" which is situated in the vicinity the city. The goddess ‘Chandi’ is the symbol of power. There is a famous fort, locally known is garh, from which the city was named Chandigarh.
   <br />
   The city has beautiful ancient, pre-historic and medieval past, which has given us a beautiful modern era. It was well known as Harappa, which was about 8000 years ago. Chandigarh is the capital of Punjab, which was approved in March 1948. The city is a witness of many refugees after freedom, who settled here after the partition.
    </p>
    <br />
    <h1><b>Attractions of Chandigarh</b></h1>
    <hr />
    <h3><b>Rock Garden</b></h3>
    <p>
    Rock Garden in Sector 1 is an exclusive attraction as Chandigarh. The city is also known for its artistic galleries created out of urban and industrial wastes. The raw supplies are shaped into beautiful images of human beings and animals and even trees. The garden was established by Nek Chand in 1957.
    </p>
